\v 3 \w because|strong="G1063"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w died|strong="G3588"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w your|strong="G2532"\w* \w life|strong="G2222"\w* \w has|strong="G2316"\w* \w been|strong="G2532"\w* \w hidden|strong="G2928"\w* \w with|strong="G1722"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w*.\f + \fr 3:3 \ft What does it mean to have one's life “hidden” in God? I imagine it has to do with protection and security.\f*
\v 4 \w Whenever|strong="G3752"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w*, \w our|strong="G2532"\w*\f + \fr 3:4 \ft Instead of “our”, perhaps 10% of the Greek manuscripts have ‘your’ (as in NIV, LB, TEV, etc.).\f* \w life|strong="G2222"\w*, \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w revealed|strong="G5319"\w*, \w then|strong="G2532"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w also|strong="G2532"\w* \w will|strong="G2532"\w* \w be|strong="G2532"\w* \w revealed|strong="G5319"\w* \w with|strong="G1722"\w* \w Him|strong="G3588"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w glory|strong="G1391"\w*.\f + \fr 3:4 \ft I suppose that this refers to Christ's second coming to set up His Messianic (Millennial) Kingdom.\f*
\p 
\v 5 \w Therefore|strong="G3767"\w* \w put|strong="G2532"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* death \w your|strong="G2532"\w* \w members|strong="G3196"\w* \w that|strong="G3588"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* \w on|strong="G1909"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w earth|strong="G1093"\w*:\f + \fr 3:5 \ft A curious turn of phrase, ‘members on the earth’; perhaps the point is that the things listed belong to this earth and cannot leave it. There will be nothing of the sort in Heaven.\f* \w fornication|strong="G4202"\w*, filthiness, \w passion|strong="G3806"\w*, \w evil|strong="G2556"\w* \w desire|strong="G1939"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w greediness|strong="G4124"\w* \w that|strong="G3588"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w idolatry|strong="G1495"\w*.\f + \fr 3:5 \ft That is what the Text says, “the greediness that is idolatry”, which leads me to suppose that there may be a greediness that is not, but I do not know which it might be.\f*
\v 6 \w Because|strong="G1223"\w* \w of|strong="G5207"\w* \w these|strong="G3739"\w* \w things|strong="G3588"\w* \w the|strong="G1909"\w* \w wrath|strong="G3709"\w* \w of|strong="G5207"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w coming|strong="G2064"\w* \w upon|strong="G1909"\w* \w the|strong="G1909"\w* \w sons|strong="G5207"\w* \w of|strong="G5207"\w* \w the|strong="G1909"\w* disobedience,\f + \fr 3:6 \ft “The sons of the disobedience” is a Pauline phrase that he also uses in Ephesians 2:2 and 5:6. The reference is to people who are characterized by disobedience to God; they have deliberately chosen the side of evil, and therefore are worthy candidates for God's wrath. Perhaps 1% of the Greek manuscripts, of objectively inferior quality, omit “upon the sons of the disobedience” (as in NIV, NASB, LB, etc.).\f*
\v 7 \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w which|strong="G3739"\w* \w things|strong="G3778"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w yourselves|strong="G4771"\w* \w once|strong="G4218"\w* \w walked|strong="G4043"\w* \w when|strong="G3753"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w lived|strong="G2198"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w them|strong="G1722"\w*.
